Install git on system-
sudo apt-get install git

setup your username on git in the system-
git config--global user.name"shadyStan1"

setup your email on git in your system-
git config--global user.email"amaniverma04@gmail.com"

then you can create a repositry over the github by visiting the website.

Step1.
echo "# taikhana2" >> README.md

Step2.initialise the git(means telling the local machine it is a git directory)-------------->
type -> git init


to create a new file-
type-> nano "file-name.extension"

type content inside the file created
to save type-> ctrl + 'O' + Enter

to exit 
type-> ctrl + 'X'

to read file->
nano "file-name"

General step to add a file to git(STAGING)------>
git add README.md

add a commit------>
 type -> git commit -m "first commit"


connect to a remote repositry from local git repository(where to push the file)------->
  type-> git remote add origin https://github.com/shadyStan1/taikhana2.git

Step to push a file to github directory------>
git push -u origin master

to clone-
git clone sshurl


****once we create a new repository we get only one branch and it is main branch called as master

##in order to create a new branch---(******this creates an exact copy of the master branch will all the files in it)
git branch "branch-name"

##to switch to this branch---
git checkout "branch-name"



to check log(commit history)-
git log

to create more decriptive graph of the commit history-
git log --all --decorate --oneline --graph

to give a name to this command-
alias graph="git log --all --decorate --oneline --graph"

then directly we can use this command 


What is pull request?
Pull requests let you tell others about changes you've pushed to a GitHub repository. 
Once a pull request is sent, interested parties can review the set of changes, discuss potential modifications,
and even push follow-up commits if necessary.

